[
    {
        "content": "<p>I noticed that the WIT format allows for a package name with a version. Is it possible to define  multiple versions at once, and allow them to both function at the same time?</p>\n<p>Initially I was thinking that I would store the expected \"api version\" alongside the binary, and then, based on that, decide which wit file to use (named things like <code>apiv1.wit</code>, <code>apiv2.wit</code>, etc.). But if I'm able to avoid that by using package versions, that would be nice.</p>\n<p>The problem is, I'm struggling to find much info on it. Any direction on this would be appreciated.</p>",
        "id": 424462037,
        "sender_full_name": "CircuitSacul",
        "timestamp": 1709429771
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, multiple versions of the same package are allowed. You'll need to split them across folders, though, as each package has a single logical version and packages are defined in the same directory right now, so you'd need something like <code>deps/v1/myapi.wit</code> and <code>deps/v2/myapi.wit</code></p>",
        "id": 424528384,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1709487647
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>is it possible to combine this with wasmtime::component::bindgen!()? I want to detect the version expected by a wasm binary and then use the correct apis, if possible</p>",
        "id": 424537592,
        "sender_full_name": "CircuitSacul",
        "timestamp": 1709494841
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yes, you'll get a trait-per-version to implement and corresponding <code>add_to_linker</code> functions</p>",
        "id": 424538307,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1709495474
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Awesome. One last question, if the host system has v1.1.0, but the guest code uses a previous 1.0.0, will it still work? Like, if I make changes to the API that are backward-compatible, is it ok if the versions don't match exactly (like minor/patch bumps)? Or do I need to keep every specific version until I'm ready to deprecate/remove it?</p>",
        "id": 424538614,
        "sender_full_name": "CircuitSacul",
        "timestamp": 1709495694
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>With <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/7994\">this PR</a>, yes, but that PR isn't in 18.0.2, it'll be in 19.0.0</p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/7994\" style=\"background-image: url(https\\:\\/\\/uploads\\.zulipusercontent\\.net\\/9163daf774003ef209eb5566d859ee38bcf92352\\/68747470733a2f2f6f70656e67726170682e6769746875626173736574732e636f6d2f323162343932323062333861316135333661636563386365383436383964353134636231363631663433333066616163383366346365396437343236313062622f62797465636f6465616c6c69616e63652f7761736d74696d652f70756c6c2f37393934)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/7994\" title=\"Make `component::Linker` semver-aware by alexcrichton 路 Pull Request #7994 路 bytecodealliance/wasmtime\">Make `component::Linker` semver-aware by alexcrichton 路 Pull Request #7994 路 bytecodealliance/wasmtime</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">This commit is an implementation of #7860 for Wasmtime where wasmtime::component::Linker is now \"semver aware\". This means that it assumes that hosts are always managing WIT interfaces in a semver-...</div></div></div>",
        "id": 424539386,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1709496312
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Got it, thanks. Is there any roadmap, or release schedule, for 19.0.0 that you're aware of?</p>",
        "id": 424539522,
        "sender_full_name": "CircuitSacul",
        "timestamp": 1709496426
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>you can read about the release process <a href=\"https://docs.wasmtime.dev/stability-release.html\">here</a>, and the answer you're looking for is \"March 20\"</p>",
        "id": 424539897,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1709496734
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm struggling to get this to work with wasmtime bindgen. I've tried this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"wit\"><pre><span></span><code>wit/deps/\n    v0/\n        api.wit\n     v1/\n        api.wit\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">bindgen</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But it just errors out:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span>: <span class=\"nc\">failed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">parse</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">package</span>: <span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Users</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">circuitsacul</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">src</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">wasmbot</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">wasmbot</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">runtime</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">wit</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">       </span><span class=\"n\">Caused</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">by</span>:\n           <span class=\"nc\">no</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">package</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">header</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">was</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">any</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WIT</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">package</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Both the api.wit files have a package header (one is @0.1.0, the other is @1.0.0). I also tried adding another top-level wit file and <code>use</code>ing the api package, but it couldn't find the package by name.</p>\n<p>What does work is using <code>bindgen!()</code> and referring to the path specifically, but I can't do that for two versions of the same package because the generated code would conflict (in particular, the struct name and the package:name).</p>\n<p>What am I doing wrong here?</p>",
        "id": 424670178,
        "sender_full_name": "CircuitSacul",
        "timestamp": 1709563240
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok I think I have a solution. I'll see if it actually works later when I try to run some wasm, but this is what I did:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">wit</span><span class=\"o\">/</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">v0</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">api</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"mf\">0.1.0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">v1</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">api</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"mf\">1.0.0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">mod</span> <span class=\"nn\">v0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wasmtime</span>::<span class=\"n\">component</span>::<span class=\"n\">bindgen</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">bindgen</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">({</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">path</span>: <span class=\"s\">\"wit/v0\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">async</span>: <span class=\"nc\">true</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"k\">mod</span> <span class=\"nn\">v1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wasmtime</span>::<span class=\"n\">component</span>::<span class=\"n\">bindgen</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">bindgen</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">({</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">path</span>: <span class=\"s\">\"wit/v1\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">async</span>: <span class=\"nc\">true</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">State</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v0</span>::<span class=\"n\">wasmbot</span>::<span class=\"n\">api</span>::<span class=\"n\">host</span>::<span class=\"n\">Host</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">State</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v1</span>::<span class=\"n\">wasmbot</span>::<span class=\"n\">api</span>::<span class=\"n\">host</span>::<span class=\"n\">Host</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">State</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now I just need to figure out how to determine which bindings to use. I suspect that <code>v0::Api::instantiate_async</code> will return an error if the guest package is using a newer version of the api? Or should I just store the expected package version separately?</p>",
        "id": 424674446,
        "sender_full_name": "CircuitSacul",
        "timestamp": 1709564293
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh that works as well, yeah, but the first error is that, for now at least, you need at least a dummy <code>*.wit</code> file in the \"root\" folder as <code>wit/$something.wit</code>, and then the <code>deps</code> folder will get read</p>",
        "id": 424682320,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1709566161
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I get the same error doing that. Does something special need to be written in the dummy wit file?</p>",
        "id": 424687723,
        "sender_full_name": "CircuitSacul",
        "timestamp": 1709567652
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code>#<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wit</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">deps</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">v0</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">api</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wit</span>\n<span class=\"n\">package</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wasmbot</span>:<span class=\"nc\">api</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"mf\">0.1.0</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">world</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">api</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">host</span>: <span class=\"nc\">interface</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">export</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guest</span>: <span class=\"nc\">interface</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">on</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">deploy</span>: <span class=\"nc\">func</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">on</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">ws</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">msg</span>: <span class=\"nc\">func</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">on</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">timer</span>: <span class=\"nc\">func</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code>#<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wit</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">dummy</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">empty</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">bindgen</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">({</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">async</span>: <span class=\"nc\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span>: <span class=\"nc\">failed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">parse</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">package</span>: <span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Users</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">circuitsacul</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">src</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">wasmbot</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">wasmbot</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">runtime</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">wit</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">       </span><span class=\"n\">Caused</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">by</span>:\n           <span class=\"nc\">no</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">package</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">header</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">was</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">any</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WIT</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">package</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 424688125,
        "sender_full_name": "CircuitSacul",
        "timestamp": 1709567792
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ah yeah, sorry, you'll need at least a dummy <code>package foo:bar;</code> in the <code>dummy.wit</code>f ile</p>",
