    {
        "content": "<p>Doing that gives this error</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span>: <span class=\"nc\">no</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">worlds</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">package</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">dummy</span>:<span class=\"nc\">dummy</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Trying <code>bindgen!({world: \"api\"})</code> just says that the world \"api\" doesn't exist in this package</p>",
        "id": 424688544,
        "sender_full_name": "CircuitSacul",
        "timestamp": 1709567888
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think it's fine though, my method worked and I don't see any big downsides to that approach</p>",
        "id": 424688726,
        "sender_full_name": "CircuitSacul",
        "timestamp": 1709567955
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ah yes, for that you'd specify <code>world: \"wasmbot:api/api@0.1.0\"</code></p>",
